        {6,3,1,4,7,0,2,5}, {6,3,1,7,5,0,2,4}, {6,4,2,0,5,7,1,3}, {7,1,3,0,6,4,2,5},
        {7,1,4,2,0,6,3,5}, {7,2,0,5,1,4,6,3}, {7,3,0,2,5,1,6,4}
    }};

    std::vector<std::pair<int, int>> initialQueens;
    std::bitset<92> validSolutionsMask;

    void initializeLookupTable() {
        // For each solution, mark which queen positions it contains
        for (int sol = 0; sol < 92; sol++) {
            for (int row = 0; row < BOARD_SIZE; row++) {
                int col = allSolutions[sol][row];
                solutionLookup[row][col].set(sol);
            }
        }
    }

public:
    EightQueensSolver() {
        initializeLookupTable();
        // Start with all solutions valid
        validSolutionsMask.set(); // Set all 92 bits to 1
    }

    bool loadInitialPositions(const std::string& filename) {
        try {
            std::ifstream file(filename);
            if (!file.is_open()) {
                std::cerr << "Error: Unable to open file " << filename << std::endl;
                return false;
            }

            json j;
            file >> j;

            initialQueens.clear();
            for (const auto& position : j["queen_positions"]) {
                int row = position["row"];
                int col = position["col"];

                // Validate boundaries
                if (row < 0 || row >= BOARD_SIZE || col < 0 || col >= BOARD_SIZE) {
                    std::cerr << "Error: Queen position (" << row << "," << col << ") is outside board boundaries" << std::endl;
                    return false;
                }

                initialQueens.push_back({row, col});
            }

            return validateInitialPositions();
        }
        catch (const std::exception& e) {
            std::cerr << "Error parsing JSON file: " << e.what() << std::endl;
            return false;
        }
    }

    bool validateInitialPositions() {
        // Check if initial queens are non-attacking
        for (size_t i = 0; i < initialQueens.size(); i++) {
            for (size_t j = i + 1; j < initialQueens.size(); j++) {
                int row1 = initialQueens[i].first, col1 = initialQueens[i].second;
                int row2 = initialQueens[j].first, col2 = initialQueens[j].second;

                // Check if queens attack each other
                if (row1 == row2 || col1 == col2 || 
                    std::abs(row1 - row2) == std::abs(col1 - col2)) {
                    std::cerr << "Error: Initial queens at positions (" << row1 << "," << col1 << ") and ("
                              << row2 << "," << col2 << ") are attacking each other" << std::endl;
                    return false;
                }
            }
        }
        return true;
    }

    std::vector<std::array<int, BOARD_SIZE>> solve() {
        // O(1) operation since we're using precomputed solutions
        // Reset valid solutions
        validSolutionsMask.set();  // All solutions initially valid

        // Apply constraints from initial queens - O(1) for fixed number of queens
        for (const auto& queen : initialQueens) {
            int row = queen.first;
            int col = queen.second;
            // Only keep solutions that have a queen at this position
            validSolutionsMask &= solutionLookup[row][col];
        }

        // Convert mask to solution vectors - O(1) because 8-Queens has finite solutions
        std::vector<std::array<int, BOARD_SIZE>> validSolutions;
        for (int i = 0; i < 92; i++) {
            if (validSolutionsMask.test(i)) {
                validSolutions.push_back(allSolutions[i]);
            }
        }

        return validSolutions;
    }

    void printSolutions(const std::vector<std::array<int, BOARD_SIZE>>& solutions) {
        if (solutions.empty()) {
            std::cout << "No solutions found." << std::endl;
            return;
        }

        std::cout << "Found " << solutions.size() << " solutions:" << std::endl;

        for (size_t s = 0; s < solutions.size(); s++) {
            std::cout << "Solution " << (s + 1) << ":" << std::endl;

            for (int i = 0; i < BOARD_SIZE; i++) {
                for (int j = 0; j < BOARD_SIZE; j++) {
                    if (solutions[s][i] == j) {
                        std::cout << "Q ";
                    } else {
                        std::cout << ". ";
                    }
                }
                std::cout << std::endl;
            }
            std::cout << std::endl;
        }
    }
};

int main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
    if (argc != 2) {
        std::cerr << "Usage: " << argv[0] << " <json_config_file>" << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }

    EightQueensSolver solver;
    if (!solver.loadInitialPositions(argv[1])) {
        return 1;
    }

    auto solutions = solver.solve();
    solver.printSolutions(solutions);

    return 0;
}

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <stdexcept>

template <typename T>
class PriorityQueue {
private:
    std::vector<T> heap;

    void heapifyUp(int index) {
        int parent = (index - 1) / 2;
        while (index > 0 && heap[index] < heap[parent]) {
            std::swap(heap[index], heap[parent]);
            index = parent;
            parent = (index - 1) / 2;
        }
    }

    void heapifyDown(int index) {
        int smallest = index;
        int left = 2 * index + 1;
        int right = 2 * index + 2;

        if (left < heap.size() && heap[left] < heap[smallest])
            smallest = left;

        if (right < heap.size() && heap[right] < heap[smallest])
            smallest = right;

        if (smallest != index) {
            std::swap(heap[index], heap[smallest]);
            heapifyDown(smallest);
        }
    }

public:
    PriorityQueue() {}

    void insert(const T& value) {
        heap.push_back(value);
        heapifyUp(heap.size() - 1);
    }

    T getMin() const {
        if (heap.empty())
            throw std::underflow_error("Priority queue is empty");
        return heap[0];
    }

    T extractMin() {
        if (heap.empty())
            throw std::underflow_error("Priority queue is empty");

        T min = heap[0];
        heap[0] = heap.back();
        heap.pop_back();

        if (!heap.empty())
            heapifyDown(0);

        return min;
    }

    bool isEmpty() const {
        return heap.empty();
    }

    size_t size() const {
        return heap.size();
    }
};

int main() {
    PriorityQueue<int> pq;

    pq.insert(5);
    pq.insert(3);
    pq.insert(7);
    pq.insert(1);

    try {
        std::cout << "Min element: " << pq.getMin() << std::endl;

        while (!pq.isEmpty()) {
            std::cout << "Extracted: " << pq.extractMin() << std::endl;
        }

        // This should throw an underflow exception
        std::cout << pq.extractMin() << std::endl;
    }
    catch (const std::underflow_error& e) {
        std::cout << "Exception caught: " << e.what() << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}

function sortByKey(arr, key) {
    return [...arr].sort((a, b) => {
        if (a[key] < b[key]) return -1;
        if (a[key] > b[key]) return 1;
        return 0;
    });
}

def binary_search(arr, target):
    left = 0
    right = len(arr) - 1

    while left <= right:
        mid = left + (right - left) // 2

        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid - 1

    return -1

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>

struct Point {
    double x, y;
    int id;
};

double distance(const Point& p1, const Point& p2) {
    return sqrt(pow(p1.x - p2.x, 2) + pow(p1.y - p2.y, 2));
}

int main() {
    std::vector<Point> coffeeShops;
    int n;
    double userX, userY;

    // Input number of coffee shops
    std::cout << "Enter number of coffee shops: ";
    std::cin >> n;

    // Input coordinates for each coffee shop
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        Point shop;
        std::cout << "Enter coordinates for coffee shop " << i + 1 << " (x y): ";
        std::cin >> shop.x >> shop.y;
        shop.id = i + 1;
        coffeeShops.push_back(shop);
    }

    // Input user location
    std::cout << "Enter your location (x y): ";
    std::cin >> userX >> userY;
    Point userLocation = {userX, userY, 0};

    // Sort coffee shops by distance to user (O(n log n) time complexity)
    std::sort(coffeeShops.begin(), coffeeShops.end(), [&userLocation](const Point& a, const Point& b) {
        return distance(a, userLocation) < distance(b, userLocation);
    });

    // The closest coffee shop is now at the beginning of the sorted vector
    std::cout << "The nearest coffee shop is shop " << coffeeShops[0].id 
              << " at coordinates (" << coffeeShops[0].x << ", " << coffeeShops[0].y << ")\n";
    std::cout << "Distance: " << distance(coffeeShops[0], userLocation) << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

public int maxSubarraySum(int[] nums) {
    if (nums == null || nums.length == 0) {
        return 0;
    }

    int maxSoFar = nums[0];
    int maxEndingHere = nums[0];

    for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
        maxEndingHere = Math.max(nums[i], maxEndingHere + nums[i]);
        maxSoFar = Math.max(maxSoFar, maxEndingHere);
    }

    return maxSoFar;
}

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <cstring>
#include <limits>
#include <algorithm>

class TravelingSalesmanSolver {
private:
    int n;
    std::vector<std::vector<int>> distances;
    std::vector<std::vector<int>> dp;
    std::vector<std::vector<int>> next;

public:
    TravelingSalesmanSolver(const std::vector<std::vector<int>>& dist) : distances(dist) {
        n = distances.size();
        dp.resize(1 << n, std::vector<int>(n, -1));
        next.resize(1 << n, std::vector<int>(n, -1));
    }

    int solve(int mask, int pos) {
        if (mask == ((1 << n) - 1)) {
            return distances[pos][0]; // Return to starting city
        }

        if (dp[mask][pos] != -1) {
            return dp[mask][pos];
        }

        int ans = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
        for (int city = 0; city < n; city++) {
            if ((mask & (1 << city)) == 0) {
                int newAns = distances[pos][city] + solve(mask | (1 << city), city);
                if (newAns < ans) {
                    ans = newAns;
                    next[mask][pos] = city;
                }
            }
        }

        dp[mask][pos] = ans;
        return ans;
    }

    std::vector<int> getPath() {
        std::vector<int> path;
        int mask = 1; // Start at city 0
        int pos = 0;

        path.push_back(0);

        while (mask != (1 << n) - 1) {
            int nextCity = next[mask][pos];
            path.push_back(nextCity);
            mask |= (1 << nextCity);
            pos = nextCity;
        }

        path.push_back(0); // Return to starting city
        return path;
    }
};

int main() {
    int n;
    std::cout << "Enter the number of cities: ";
    std::cin >> n;

    std::vector<std::vector<int>> distances(n, std::vector<int>(n));
    std::cout << "Enter the distance matrix:" << std::endl;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            std::cin >> distances[i][j];
        }
    }

    TravelingSalesmanSolver solver(distances);
    int minDistance = solver.solve(1, 0);

    std::cout << "Minimum distance: " << minDistance << std::endl;

    std::vector<int> optimalPath = solver.getPath();
    std::cout << "Optimal path: ";
    for (int city : optimalPath) {
        std::cout << city << " ";
    }
    std::cout << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
